<recipe>
<title>
Greek Zoodles Recipe
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: I Heart Eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
COOK TIME: 20 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 30 minutes
COURSE: Main Course
CUISINE: American, Greek
KEYWORD: Ground beef, zucchini
SERVINGS: 4 servings
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="0.5 lb ">Beef</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0">Bell Pepper</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0">Red Onion</ingredient><ingredient amount="4.0">Garlic</ingredient><ingredient amount="14.5 oz ">Tomato</ingredient><ingredient amount="14.0 oz ">Tomato</ingredient><ingredient amount="6.0 oz ">Tomato Paste</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 C ">Olive</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 C ">Cheese</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
In a large skillet, cook the beef until browned; drain.
Add peppers and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink.
Stir in garlic, and cook for 30 seconds.
Add tomatoes, crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano, and salt and pepper to taste. Stir to combine.
Let simmer for 10 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
While sauce is simmering, trim ends from washed zucchini.
Spiralize zucchini according to spiralizer directions.
Serve sauce over zucchini noodles (zoodles), and top with olives, feta, and fresh oregano just before serving.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American, Greek</cuisine></recipe>